HEADWORD: Three
<hw>Three</hw> <pr>(thr⟦emac⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>⟦thorn⟧re</ets>, <ets>⟦thorn⟧reo</ets>, <ets>⟦thorn⟧ri</ets>, AS.
<ets>⟦thorn⟧r⟦imac⟧</ets>, masc., <ets>⟦thorn⟧re⟦oacute⟧</ets>, fem. and
neut.; akin to OFries. <ets>thre</ets>, OS. <ets>thria</ets>,
<ets>threa</ets>, D. <ets>drie</ets>, G. <ets>drei</ets>, OHG.
<ets>dr⟦imac⟧</ets>, Icel. <ets>⟦thorn⟧r⟦imac⟧r</ets>, Dan. & Sw.
<ets>tre</ets>, Goth. <ets>⟦thorn⟧reis</ets>, Lith. <ets>trys</ets>,
Ir., Gael. & W. <ets>tri</ets>, Russ. <ets>tri</ets>, L.
<ets>tres</ets>, Gr. <grk>trei^s</grk>, Skr. <ets>tri</ets>. ⟦root⟧301.
Cf. 3d <er>Drilling</er>, <er>Tern</er>, <pos>a.</pos>, <er>Third</er>,
