<def>One more than two; two and one.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧I offer thee
<xex>three</xex> things.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>2 Sam. xxiv. 12.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Three</qex> solemn aisles approach the shrine.</q>
<rj><qau>Keble.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <ex>Three</ex> is often joined with other words, forming
